X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:10:58.056 --> 00:11:01.056 A:middle
The Inspection feature
allows you to debug

00:11:01.056 --> 00:11:04.816 A:middle
and analyze the accessibility
state of your app.

00:11:05.296 --> 00:11:07.866 A:middle
Then we have the Audit
feature to help you

00:11:07.866 --> 00:11:10.586 A:middle
to find accessibility
issues in your app.

00:11:12.296 --> 00:11:15.696 A:middle
And last we have the Settings
feature that helps you

00:11:15.696 --> 00:11:20.236 A:middle
to quickly test how accessibly
settings affect your app.

00:11:21.376 --> 00:11:25.046 A:middle
So the first one I want to talk
about is the Audit feature.

00:11:26.336 --> 00:11:29.456 A:middle
So, ultimately your goal is

00:11:29.516 --> 00:11:32.556 A:middle
to make sure your app is
accessible to everyone.

00:11:33.206 --> 00:11:36.396 A:middle
And to do that you need
to first audit your app.

00:11:36.736 --> 00:11:39.186 A:middle
Now, earlier Susumu
mentioned it would be awesome

00:11:39.186 --> 00:11:43.406 A:middle
if you could actually run with
VoiceOver or Switch control

00:11:43.586 --> 00:11:44.786 A:middle
and audit your app that way.

00:11:45.796 --> 00:11:48.466 A:middle
Or you could also hire an
accessibility consultant

00:11:48.466 --> 00:11:50.056 A:middle
to do the evaluation
on your behalf.

00:11:50.746 --> 00:11:54.196 A:middle
