00:18:17.846 --> 00:18:22.696 A:middle
So what you've just seen is how
the Audit feature can help you

00:18:22.736 --> 00:18:25.936 A:middle
auto-detect problems
in your app.

00:18:25.936 --> 00:18:27.646 A:middle
It could give you
suggested solution.

00:18:27.986 --> 00:18:30.526 A:middle
And even speed up the process
of reporting those bugs.

00:18:32.906 --> 00:18:36.006 A:middle
As powerful and as
great as this feature is

00:18:36.046 --> 00:18:39.676 A:middle
in helping you detect
issues in your app,

00:18:39.676 --> 00:18:44.436 A:middle
similar to the compile
warnings in Xcode,

00:18:45.776 --> 00:18:49.906 A:middle
having no warning does not
mean your app doesn't have

00:18:50.116 --> 00:18:50.706 A:middle
any problem.

00:18:51.586 --> 00:18:53.306 A:middle
So that's why it's
important for you to do some

00:18:53.306 --> 00:18:55.366 A:middle
of that manual auditing
yourself.

00:18:55.886 --> 00:19:00.826 A:middle
And to show you why
this is important,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:18:55.886 --> 00:19:00.826 A:middle
And to show you why
this is important,

00:19:01.206 --> 00:19:03.046 A:middle
let me give you an example.

00:19:03.686 --> 00:19:07.136 A:middle
So, suppose you have a button

00:19:07.786 --> 00:19:09.566 A:middle
and its function
is to send a mail.

00:19:10.446 --> 00:19:13.046 A:middle
Of course, the button comes
with a bunch of properties.

00:19:14.676 --> 00:19:16.956 A:middle
One thing we tend to
like to do when we want

00:19:16.956 --> 00:19:19.966 A:middle
to create a new button
is we simply take one

00:19:19.966 --> 00:19:22.596 A:middle
of these existing button
and we duplicate it.

00:19:22.596 --> 00:19:25.836 A:middle
And of course, that
means all the properties

00:19:26.156 --> 00:19:27.566 A:middle
of that button gets transferred.

00:19:28.876 --> 00:19:31.016 A:middle
And we go and tweak
some of the properties

00:19:31.016 --> 00:19:35.296 A:middle
like the actions and the icons.

00:19:36.026 --> 00:19:37.136 A:middle
That's fine.

00:19:37.956 --> 00:19:38.896 A:middle
That's all good.

00:19:39.006 --> 00:19:44.176 A:middle
Except if you forget to
update some of the property,

00:19:44.176 --> 00:19:45.056 A:middle
that could be a problem.

00:19:45.356 --> 00:19:46.486 A:middle
Especially in this case,

00:19:46.536 --> 00:19:48.656 A:middle
it's the accessibility
label property.

00:19:50.566 --> 00:19:52.816 A:middle
For assistive clients
like VoiceOver,

00:19:53.486 --> 00:19:56.476 A:middle
the accessibility label
property is super important.

00:19:56.476 --> 00:19:59.226 A:middle
Because that's the only
piece of information it has

00:19:59.226 --> 00:20:01.386 A:middle
about how this button functions.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:19:59.226 --> 00:20:01.386 A:middle
about how this button functions.

00:20:02.946 --> 00:20:06.926 A:middle
So, if an assistive client
like VoiceOver were to land

00:20:06.926 --> 00:20:10.366 A:middle
on this button, and you haven't
updated the accessibility label,

00:20:10.366 --> 00:20:11.926 A:middle
it still says Send Mail.

00:20:11.926 --> 00:20:14.866 A:middle
But they're going to
press a button thinking

00:20:14.866 --> 00:20:15.806 A:middle
that they're sending a mail.

00:20:15.916 --> 00:20:18.466 A:middle
In fact, they've just
deleted that mail.

00:20:18.466 --> 00:20:20.596 A:middle
So that's not a great outcome.

00:20:21.226 --> 00:20:27.636 A:middle
And so for that, we're
here to help you go

00:20:27.636 --> 00:20:30.086 A:middle
through that manual
auditing using the tool.

00:20:30.466 --> 00:20:32.466 A:middle
And that's why I want to
talk about Inspection.

00:20:36.316 --> 00:20:38.916 A:middle
So let me give you some
highlights of Inspection

00:20:38.916 --> 00:20:40.266 A:middle
and show you how that helps you

00:20:40.346 --> 00:20:42.186 A:middle
through the manual
auditing process.

