00:24:52.846 --> 00:24:53.886 A:middle
to be more complex.

00:24:54.806 --> 00:24:57.186 A:middle
So to show you how this
feature works, let me go ahead

00:24:57.186 --> 00:25:00.326 A:middle
and launch the OS X
version of the same app.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:24:57.186 --> 00:25:00.326 A:middle
and launch the OS X
version of the same app.

00:25:07.426 --> 00:25:07.736 A:middle
All right?

00:25:07.916 --> 00:25:11.626 A:middle
So I have here the OS X
version of the same app.

00:25:11.916 --> 00:25:13.506 A:middle
And let's do something a
little bit more complex,

00:25:13.736 --> 00:25:14.856 A:middle
multiplication.

00:25:16.046 --> 00:25:17.926 A:middle
And so then when you
play, 3 times 6 --

00:25:17.926 --> 00:25:19.856 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Sorry, try again.

00:25:19.856 --> 00:25:20.766 A:middle
&gt;&gt; -- that, how about this?

00:25:20.766 --> 00:25:22.176 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Incorrect.

00:25:22.176 --> 00:25:22.876 A:middle
Try again.

00:25:22.876 --> 00:25:24.026 A:middle
&gt;&gt; -- 6. 18.

00:25:24.026 --> 00:25:24.476 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Correct.

00:25:25.546 --> 00:25:27.076 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Okay, so you play
the same game.

00:25:27.076 --> 00:25:28.646 A:middle
And you know, this app works.

00:25:29.116 --> 00:25:32.446 A:middle
We have the same version
app running on iOS and OS X.

00:25:32.446 --> 00:25:32.616 A:middle
All right.

00:25:33.436 --> 00:25:38.156 A:middle
So the first thing you
want to do is tell the tool

00:25:38.156 --> 00:25:41.046 A:middle
that you're inspecting
this new app.

00:25:42.006 --> 00:25:45.136 A:middle
So, we're going to go
and select my MacBook Pro

00:25:45.136 --> 00:25:48.056 A:middle
because we're inspecting the
desktop itself right now.

00:25:48.266 --> 00:25:50.096 A:middle
And in this case we
could also select

00:25:50.156 --> 00:25:51.516 A:middle
which app we want to inspect.

00:25:51.896 --> 00:25:53.216 A:middle
So I'm going to pick
the Math Learner.

00:25:53.776 --> 00:25:59.076 A:middle
And again, we could run Audit
and see what issues we find.

00:25:59.466 --> 00:26:00.726 A:middle
And it found a bunch of issues.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:25:59.466 --> 00:26:00.726 A:middle
And it found a bunch of issues.

00:26:01.806 --> 00:26:05.616 A:middle
I want to bring your attention
to these four issues here.

00:26:06.366 --> 00:26:08.276 A:middle
It says: "Potentially
inaccessible element."

00:26:08.756 --> 00:26:11.286 A:middle
So the way these answer
choices were implemented,

00:26:11.286 --> 00:26:14.136 A:middle
they were simply custom NSview.

00:26:14.666 --> 00:26:17.206 A:middle
That's drawing those
text via CA text layers.

00:26:18.106 --> 00:26:21.246 A:middle
Now, by default, CA layers
have no accessibility support.

00:26:21.876 --> 00:26:23.206 A:middle
Which means if you create them,

00:26:24.086 --> 00:26:27.266 A:middle
clients like VoiceOver is not
going to be able to see them.

00:26:27.266 --> 00:26:29.066 A:middle
And so the tool is
telling you that right now,

00:26:29.376 --> 00:26:30.596 A:middle
that these are not accessible.

00:26:30.596 --> 00:26:33.336 A:middle
So to understand
how to fix this up,

00:26:33.336 --> 00:26:36.626 A:middle
it helps to know how the
accessibility hierarchy works.

00:26:38.196 --> 00:26:39.626 A:middle
So let's go to the Inspection.

00:26:40.166 --> 00:26:43.916 A:middle
And again, I'm going to
turn on Inspection Pointer.

00:26:44.976 --> 00:26:47.866 A:middle
And so if I bring my
mouse over and, again,

00:26:47.866 --> 00:26:49.646 A:middle
it's going to inspect
whatever's under my mouse.

00:26:50.156 --> 00:26:50.966 A:middle
What I'm interested

00:26:50.966 --> 00:26:53.566 A:middle
in to inspect right now
is the entire window.

00:26:54.496 --> 00:26:56.656 A:middle
And the reason is
because I want to know

00:26:56.916 --> 00:26:59.936 A:middle
who are the children
of this window.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:27:00.566 --> 00:27:04.686 A:middle
So, the way I could I look
at that is I could look

00:27:05.266 --> 00:27:07.066 A:middle
under the hierarchy
section here.

00:27:07.646 --> 00:27:12.756 A:middle
And then here are all the
children of this window.

00:27:13.346 --> 00:27:16.366 A:middle
So, I'm on the equation.

00:27:16.366 --> 00:27:17.656 A:middle
You can see that red highlight.

00:27:18.426 --> 00:27:19.746 A:middle
On the image.

00:27:20.726 --> 00:27:21.966 A:middle
Some status text.

00:27:21.966 --> 00:27:25.136 A:middle
And a bunch of stuff in
the Tool Bar section.

00:27:25.906 --> 00:27:30.516 A:middle
So right now, those four crucial
answer choice buttons do not

00:27:30.516 --> 00:27:32.446 A:middle
exist as children of the window.

00:27:33.816 --> 00:27:35.496 A:middle
And so we know we need
to go and fix it up.

00:27:35.956 --> 00:27:38.106 A:middle
But today I'm not going to
show you how to fix it up.

00:27:39.076 --> 00:27:41.256 A:middle
Instead, I'm going to refer you

00:27:41.256 --> 00:27:44.926 A:middle
to our sample code
accessibility UI example.

00:27:45.506 --> 00:27:47.916 A:middle
It's something to download
from developer.apple.com.

00:27:48.696 --> 00:27:51.006 A:middle
This sample app contains
a whole library

00:27:51.006 --> 00:27:52.696 A:middle
with different UI scenarios

00:27:53.086 --> 00:27:56.116 A:middle
and how you could add
accessibly support for those.

00:27:56.906 --> 00:27:58.166 A:middle
So I encourage you to do that.

00:27:58.986 --> 00:28:01.676 A:middle
And once you fix it up, I expect


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:27:58.986 --> 00:28:01.676 A:middle
And once you fix it up, I expect

00:28:01.786 --> 00:28:05.986 A:middle
that those four answer choice
buttons should then appear

00:28:05.986 --> 00:28:08.136 A:middle
as children of this window.

00:28:08.356 --> 00:28:11.516 A:middle
So you could verify
it in this hierarchy.

00:28:17.156 --> 00:28:18.866 A:middle
So, what I've shown you

00:28:18.866 --> 00:28:21.816 A:middle
so far is how you can use
the Inspection feature

00:28:21.816 --> 00:28:24.296 A:middle
to help you do some of
that manual auditing.

00:28:25.106 --> 00:28:27.416 A:middle
And also how you could
use Inspection feature

00:28:27.716 --> 00:28:30.136 A:middle
to do some more debugging
and analysis

00:28:30.136 --> 00:28:31.966 A:middle
of the accessibility
state of your app.

00:28:33.136 --> 00:28:39.246 A:middle
The next thing I want to
talk about is Settings.

00:28:39.726 --> 00:28:43.336 A:middle
So, on every OS platform
we have many,

00:28:43.336 --> 00:28:45.106 A:middle
many accessibility settings.

00:28:45.536 --> 00:28:47.126 A:middle
That comes built right in.

00:28:48.026 --> 00:28:54.486 A:middle
So for example, on the
iPhone, in the Settings app

00:28:54.756 --> 00:28:58.786 A:middle
under General Accessibility
you're going to find many,

00:28:58.786 --> 00:29:01.546 A:middle
many wonderful accessibility
features built right in.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:28:58.786 --> 00:29:01.546 A:middle
many wonderful accessibility
features built right in.

00:29:02.106 --> 00:29:04.146 A:middle
And settings like Toggle.

00:29:04.786 --> 00:29:09.006 A:middle
So let's say if you want to
know how Dynamic Font affects

00:29:09.006 --> 00:29:09.926 A:middle
your app.

00:29:09.926 --> 00:29:15.206 A:middle
You could go in, adjust the font
size to something really large.

00:29:16.086 --> 00:29:16.806 A:middle
Then go back to your app.

00:29:18.066 --> 00:29:21.526 A:middle
And then visually verify how a
large font looks in your app.

00:29:22.256 --> 00:29:24.016 A:middle
Then you could go back
to the Settings app.

00:29:25.856 --> 00:29:27.926 A:middle
Readjust to something
really small.

00:29:28.456 --> 00:29:35.406 A:middle
Then see how a small
font appears in your app.

00:29:35.686 --> 00:29:38.936 A:middle
Now, you could see that this
could become quite tedious

00:29:38.936 --> 00:29:41.936 A:middle
if you have to constantly
switch back and forth

00:29:42.306 --> 00:29:45.746 A:middle
between the Settings
app and your app.

00:29:45.746 --> 00:29:47.906 A:middle
And how do you know

00:29:47.906 --> 00:29:51.526 A:middle
which accessibility settings
are important to test?

00:29:53.096 --> 00:29:58.376 A:middle
Well, our tool will
answer that for you.

00:29:59.036 --> 00:30:02.096 A:middle
So, here's our Settings tab.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:29:59.036 --> 00:30:02.096 A:middle
So, here's our Settings tab.

00:30:02.446 --> 00:30:06.686 A:middle
Our Settings tab
now present you some

00:30:06.686 --> 00:30:09.716 A:middle
of the most common
accessibility settings

00:30:09.776 --> 00:30:10.876 A:middle
that we want you to test.

00:30:12.586 --> 00:30:14.546 A:middle
In addition, since it's
built right into the tool,

00:30:15.226 --> 00:30:16.576 A:middle
you no longer have to
switch back and forth

00:30:16.576 --> 00:30:19.176 A:middle
between the Settings
app and your app.

00:30:20.516 --> 00:30:25.016 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:30:25.516 --> 00:30:28.266 A:middle
And here's a demo to
show you that can work.

00:30:29.316 --> 00:30:31.896 A:middle
So in the Settings tab, now
you can invert the colors.

00:30:32.406 --> 00:30:36.416 A:middle
And immediately see the
effect it has on your app.

00:30:37.356 --> 00:30:39.526 A:middle
And we could do the same
thing with the font size.

00:30:40.076 --> 00:30:40.706 A:middle
Adjust it.

00:30:41.886 --> 00:30:43.486 A:middle
And see it directly.

00:30:54.716 --> 00:30:59.836 A:middle
So, what you've just seen is
how cool the Settings feature is


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:31:00.336 --> 00:31:01.556 A:middle
to make it easier for you.

00:31:02.226 --> 00:31:04.646 A:middle
So, today I've shown you
our three major features.

00:31:05.966 --> 00:31:09.096 A:middle
The first is the Audit
feature, that help you

00:31:09.096 --> 00:31:11.866 A:middle
to autodetect accessibility
issues in your app,

00:31:13.226 --> 00:31:14.866 A:middle
give you suggestions
on how to fix it.

00:31:15.526 --> 00:31:17.746 A:middle
And make it faster for you
to report those issues.

00:31:20.576 --> 00:31:23.616 A:middle
Then we saw how great
the Inspection feature is

00:31:23.976 --> 00:31:26.356 A:middle
to guide you through that
process of manual auditing

00:31:27.166 --> 00:31:29.406 A:middle
and allow you to do
debugging analysis

00:31:29.456 --> 00:31:32.296 A:middle
of the accessibility
state of your app.

00:31:32.606 --> 00:31:35.076 A:middle
And last, you just saw
the Settings feature

00:31:35.076 --> 00:31:37.006 A:middle
that will make it
much easier for you

00:31:37.006 --> 00:31:41.346 A:middle
to test how accessibility
settings changes affect

00:31:41.536 --> 00:31:41.816 A:middle
your app.

00:31:43.406 --> 00:31:49.476 A:middle
And that is the quick look
of Accessibility Inspector.

00:31:50.516 --> 00:31:55.736 A:middle
[ Applause ]

